The paper focuses on the dynamics of online social systems and the impact of content quality on user engagement, which suggests a strong connection to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of deep learning computer vision models to score images also suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). The study of how image beauty is distributed over a large-scale social system could also be relevant to the sub-category of social and economic systems (cs.SD) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the practical implications for improving link recommender systems suggest a connection to the sub-category of social computing (cs.SOC).
